# Onboarding Engine – Run Guide

## Prerequisites

### 1. Install Node.js (LTS)
Download from: https://nodejs.org

Verify:
node -v  
npm -v

---

### 2. Install Angular CLI (global)
npm install -g @angular/cli

Verify:
ng version

---

### 3. Install Python (for serving built files)
Download from: https://www.python.org

Verify:
python --version

---

## Run Application (Mock Mode – Default)

### 1. Install dependencies
npm install

### 2. Start Angular dev server
ng serve

### 3. Open in browser
http://localhost:4200

Mock data will be used automatically (no backend needed).

---

## Switch to Real API

Edit:

src/environments/environment.ts

Set:
useMock: false  
baseUrl: "https://your-api-endpoint"

Restart dev server:

ng serve

---

## Build for Production

ng build --configuration production

Output folder:

dist/<project-name>/

---

## Run App Without Angular / Node

You can run the built app using only Python:

cd dist/<project-name>  
python -m http.server 4200

Open in browser:

http://localhost:4200

---

## Quick Command Reference

### Install
npm install

### Run development server
ng serve

### Build production bundle
ng build --configuration production

### Run built app using Python
cd dist/<project-name>  
python -m http.server 4200